Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine brown-buff. Circular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). Name Ion.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0423)
